The paper presents a framework for learning robust low-rank representations using structured non-convex optimization techniques and dictionary learning. This connects to several areas of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and multimedia (cs.MM). The examples presented in the paper also involve image, audio, and video processing, further supporting these potential sub-categories.
